---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = '29 april 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="privacy — michael tawiah"
  description="how mk innovations ltd handles your data when you visit michaeltawiah.com or get in touch."
>
  <Nav />

  <main id="top">
    <section class="page-hero">
      <div class="hero-glow"></div>
      <div class="page-label">privacy</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">privacy policy.</h1>
      <p class="page-tagline">last updated — {lastUpdated}</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section privacy">
      <p class="lead">
        this policy explains what personal data mk innovations ltd ("we", "i",
        "us") collects when you visit michaeltawiah.com, what we do with it,
        and the rights you have over it. we keep it short and in plain english
        so you can actually read it.
      </p>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">01 — who we are</div>
        <p>
          this site is operated by <span class="hl">mk innovations ltd</span>,
          a company registered in england &amp; wales (company no.
          <span class="hl">12571567</span>). for any privacy question, email
          <a href="mailto:me@michaeltawiah.com" class="inline-link">me@michaeltawiah.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          we are the data controller for any personal data collected through
          this website.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">02 — what we collect</div>
        <p>this is a static brochure site. there are no forms, accounts or trackers. the only data that touches us is:</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li><span class="hl">server logs</span> — your ip address, user agent, referrer and the time you visited. created automatically by github pages, our host, in the normal course of serving the site.</li>
          <li><span class="hl">contact data</span> — if you email <a href="mailto:me@michaeltawiah.com" class="inline-link">me@michaeltawiah.com</a> or book a call via calendly, we receive whatever you choose to send us (name, email, message, time slot).</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          we do <span class="hl">not</span> use cookies, analytics, ad pixels
          or fingerprinting on this site.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">03 — why we use it</div>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>to keep the website online and secure (legitimate interests).</li>
          <li>to reply to enquiries and arrange calls (legitimate interests / steps to enter into a contract).</li>
          <li>where relevant, to perform a contract for performance-marketing services (contract).</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">04 — third parties</div>
        <p>we rely on a small number of processors to run the site and the business:</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li><span class="hl">github pages</span> — hosting and tls termination.</li>
          <li><span class="hl">godaddy</span> — domain registrar and dns.</li>
          <li><span class="hl">google workspace</span> — business email for me@michaeltawiah.com.</li>
          <li><span class="hl">calendly</span> — call scheduling. they collect the booking details you submit and process them under their own privacy policy.</li>
          <li><span class="hl">automatedAds</span> — separate platform we operate. governed by its own privacy policy at <a href="https://www.automated-ads.com" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">automated-ads.com</a>.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          outbound links to linkedin, instagram and youtube are governed by
          those providers' own policies once you click through.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">05 — how long we keep it</div>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>server logs: kept by our host for a short rolling window (typically 7–30 days).</li>
          <li>email correspondence: kept for as long as needed for the engagement, then archived or deleted in line with normal business records.</li>
          <li>calendly bookings: retained while the meeting is relevant; managed in calendly.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">06 — your rights</div>
        <p>under uk gdpr you can ask us to:</p>
        <ul class="list">
          <li>access the personal data we hold on you,</li>
          <li>correct it if it's wrong,</li>
          <li>delete it ("right to be forgotten"),</li>
          <li>restrict or object to how we use it,</li>
          <li>port it to another provider.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          email <a href="mailto:me@michaeltawiah.com" class="inline-link">me@michaeltawiah.com</a>
          and we'll action requests within one calendar month. you can also
          complain to the
          <a href="https://ico.org.uk" class="inline-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico</a>
          if you think we've handled your data poorly.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">07 — international transfers</div>
        <p>
          some of our processors (e.g. calendly, google) operate outside the
          uk. where personal data is transferred outside the uk/eea we rely on
          adequacy regulations or standard contractual clauses to keep it
          protected.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="block">
        <div class="block-label">08 — changes</div>
        <p>
          if this policy changes we'll update the "last updated" date at the
          top. material changes will be flagged on the homepage.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="mailto:me@michaeltawiah.com" class="cta-btn cta-btn-outline">email a privacy question</a>
        <a href="/" class="cta-btn cta-btn-outline">← back to home</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: 9rem 2rem 4rem;
    text-align: center;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero-glow {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(
      ellipse 60% 60% at 50% 50%,
      rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.08),
      transparent 70%
    );
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .page-label {
    position: relative;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .page-title {
    position: relative;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 7vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .page-tagline {
    position: relative;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .privacy {
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .lead {
    color: #b8b8b8;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0 0 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .block {
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }
  .block:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }
  .block-label {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .block p {
    color: #b8b8b8;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .list {
    color: #b8b8b8;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .list li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .cta-row {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .cta-btn-outline {
    border: 1px solid var(--fg);
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .cta-btn-outline:hover {
    background: var(--fg);
    color: #000;
  }
</style>
